  "prompt": "How much money does a Ranji Trophy cricketer earn?",
  "response": "The earnings of a Ranji Trophy cricketer can vary based on several factors such as the state association they play for, their experience, and their performance. On average, a Ranji Trophy player can earn between INR 20,000 to INR 50,000 per day of match fees. Additionally, players may receive annual retainerships from their state associations, which can range from INR 1 lakh to INR 10 lakh or more, depending on their grade and performance.\n\nIt's also worth noting that players who perform well in the Ranji Trophy may attract attention from IPL teams, which can significantly increase their earnings. However, these figures are approximate and can vary.",
